RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Special Weight Purse 43000. (INCLUDES UP TO $1,400 LTBASBF) FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $20,000 In Their Last Three Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PORTO DEL ACE was allowed to settle on the inside to midway through the final turn then angled out to four wide at the three sixteenths pole and ran down the leader to prove best. CRIMSON GLORY rushed up the rail and cut the corner into the first turn to take the lead, set an easy pace to deep stretch but was caught in the final jumps. TIME TO CLOSE prompted the pace from two or three wide while fighting gamely with HONEST DEAL to the final turn, kept on but was outfinished by outside closer. RONA VISION was unhurried to the three furlong marker then moved up to make a late rally in the stretch but was too late. SECRET GUITAR raced in the middle of the pack around the first turn then made a three wide bid at the five sixteenths pole but faltered. NATURALBORNSENDER raced five wide into the first turn then settled near the back and was not a factor. HONEST DEAL prompted the pace inside of TIME TO CLOSE to the five sixteenths pole and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Crimson Glory
ENTRY.COMMENT: rushed to lead, set pace, caught final jumps

ENTRY.NAME: Porto Del Ace
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, 4w3/16, ran down leader, best

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GEORGIA DAWN raced in the middle of the pack on the inside around the first turn, steadily advanced down the backstretch and kept on to run down the leader and drew clear late. MSCHITCHATTOUR was unhurried to the final turn then started to circle the field and was best of the rest. TEASIN' TESLA vied for the early lead from three wide to the turn and retreated. HARLANS WARRIOR pressed the pace from the two path to the three furlong marker and gave way. BEYOND THE HYPE went to a pressured lead but was through after a half.
